Because Delta is so, so contagious, the % of people who need to be vaccinated to stop it from spreading is really high. Even in SF, which at 70 percent has one of the best vaccination levels among big cities, new coronavirus cases are spiking sharply.

Covid numbers are rising in California. So I talked to some experts to try to make sense of what's going on.

The simple answer is that this summer, we loosened restrictions, the Delta variant gained a foothold and our vaccinations stalled. My latest: https://t.co/aautsodfor
